    dc:creator "Wang, Jian; Zeng, Zhao-Chi; Lyu, Zhi-Tong; Liu, Zu-Yao; Wang, Ying-Yong" ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Description of a new species of Gracixalus (Amphibia: Anura: Rhacophoridae) from Guangdong Province, southeastern China" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250891>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250889>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250893>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250887>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250895>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250897> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250891>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. The adult male holotype of Gracixalus guangdongensis sp. nov. (SYS a005724) in life. A: general aspect; B: lateral view; C: ventral view; D: showing nuptial pads with minute granules on the dorsal surface of the first finger; E: ventral view of hand; D: ventral view of foot." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1250891/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250889>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Bayesian inference tree of Gracixalus guangdongensis sp. nov. and the known congeners of the genus (except G. carinensis and G. medogensis) derived from partial DNA sequences of the mitochondrial 16S rRNA gene with Bayesian posterior probabilities (BPP>70% retained) and maximum-likelihood bootstrap values (1000 replicates; BS>60 retained), respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1250889/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250893>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Waveforms and spectrograms of the advertisement calls of Gracixalus guangdongensis sp. nov., G. jinggangensis and G. nonggangensis, respectively. A & B: The advertisement call of Gracixalus guangdongensis sp. nov. from Dawuling Forest Station; C: The advertisement call of Gracixalus guangdongensis sp. nov. from Mount Nankun; D: The advertisement call of Gracixalus guangdongensis sp. nov. from Nanling Nature Reserve. E: The advertisement call of Gracixalus jinggangensis, E1: Call with 3 notes, E2: Call with 4 notes; F: The advertisement call of Gracixalus nonggangensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1250893/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250887>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map showing the type localities of four Gracixalus species from southeastern China. Squares: localities of G. guangdongensis sp. nov.: (1): Dawuling forest station, Maoming City, Guangdong Province; (2): Mount Nankun, Huizhou City, Guangdong Province; (3): Nanling Nature Reserve, Shaoguan City, Guangdong Province and the adjacent Mangshan Nature Reserve, Yizhang City, Hunan Province. Circles: type localities of other three Gracixalus species: (4): Mt. Jinggang, Jinggangshan City, Jiangxi Province; (5): Mt. Dayao, Jinxiu County, Guangxi Province; (6): Nonggang Nature Reserve, Chongzuo City, Guangxi Province." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1250887/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250895>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitat of Gracixalus guangdongensis sp. nov. in Dawuling Forest Station, Maoming City, Guangdong Province, China." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1250895/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250897>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Ecology and behavior of Gracixalus guangdongensis sp. nov.: A: mating behavior and sexual dimorphism: a pair on the bamboo stem prior to amplexus, the male (with distinctly visible nuptial pad on the first finger) above and female (with a larger body size than the male and without nuptial pads) below; B & C: a female sitting in an open bamboo joint, filled with numerous eggs and embryos; D: different clutches of eggs in different stages of developments on the wall of an open bamboo joint." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1250897/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

